
                ESTERIAN CONQUEST(tm) README FILE (Version 1.5)

    This document offers quick installation information for Esterian
    Conquest.  If your BBS is like most, Esterian Conquest will become one
    of the most requested and used door programs you own.  Our goal is to
    create the best and most used BBS door game in existence.


    FEATURES THAT SYSOP'S LIKE ABOUT ESTERIAN CONQUEST:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

    LOW-MAINTENANCE.  Esterian Conquest is easy to install and is self-
       reliant.  Simply install the program, initialize one or more games,
       and forget about it.  This is a very well behaved program that runs
       reliably and returns to your BBS software correctly when done.

    SELF-CORRECTING.  Esterian Conquest automatically backs up the previous
       state of a game before processing moves.  It also checks the
       integrity of the data files before using them.  If any errors exist,
       it restores the previous backup so only one turn is lost at most.

    BULLETPROOF.  Esterian Conquest handles the serial communications
       hardware and interrupts.  It does not get disrupted by line noise or
       phone disconnection, nor does it miss characters typed by players.

    MULTI-NODE.  Esterian Conquest will support simultaneous multi-node
       play regardless of your BBS configuration.

    CUSTOMIZED OPERATION.  You can control many aspects of Esterian
       Conquest.  Set the maximum number of players, reserve empires for
       particular users, specify the days of the week moves are processed
       and much more (see the Sysop's Guide about the ECUTIL program).


    FEATURES THAT YOUR USERS WILL LOVE:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

    REALISTIC ACTION: Sophisticated simulations of battle, planetary
       growth, and espionage make them feel like they're really there.
       They command 7 types of ships.  They order fleets on 15 possible
       missions and they have total control of their planets: directing
       production, setting tax levels, and building defenses.

    ADVANCED, YET EASY TO USE: Well-structured menus accept commands.
       Optional ANSI graphics are available for all menus and charts.
       Multiple commands can be issued on one line -- the program will
       remember and process them.  Expert mode speeds up the game and on-
       line help is available for any menu.

    EXTRAS THAT GO THE FULL NINE YARDS:  They can send messages to other
       players with the built-in text editor.  Autopilot mode will care for
       empires if they are away for a while.  All results of their missions
       are reported in word-wrapped, realistic messages.





        ESTERIAN CONQUEST README FILE (Version 1.5)                    2


    SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS FOR ESTERIAN CONQUEST
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
       Esterian Conquest will run on any IBM PC,XT,PS/2, or compatible
       machine with the following capacities:

          MS-DOS version 2.11 or later.

          512K of internal memory (640K is recommended for larger games
          involving 25 players).

          A hard disk with at least 1MB available disk space.

          BBS software that can generate any of the following door file
          formats:

             PCBOARD.SYS  . . . . (PCBoard v14+)
             DOOR.SYS   . . . . . (as suggested by GAP software)
             DORINFOx.DEF . . . . (QBBS, RBBS, RA, FoReM, etc.)
             CALLINFO.BBS . . . . (Wildcat!)
             SFDOORS.DAT. . . . . (Spitfire)
             CHAIN.TXT  . . . . . (WWIV)
             INFO.BBS . . . . . . (Phoenix software)


    FILES ON THE PROGRAM DISKETTE
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
       ECUTIL.EXE ..... Esterian Conquest Sysop Utility.
       ECGAME.EXE ..... The User Interface.
       ECMAINT.EXE .... The Maintenance Program.

       WHATSNEW.DOC ... Changes or updates to Esterian Conquest.
       ECREADME.DOC ... This brief installation document for sysops.
       ECSYSOP.DOC  ... Esterian Conquest Sysops Guide.
       ECQSTART.DOC ... Quick start document for players.
       ECPLAYER.DOC ... Esterian Conquest players' Guide.


    INSTALLING ESTERIAN CONQUEST
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
       Esterian Conquest is easily installed in four steps: (1) Copy
       program files into a directory, (2) Create a door-game batch file to
       run the Esterian Conquest game when requested by users, (3) Add
       commands to run the Maintenance Program (ECMAINT) to your BBS daily
       event batch file, and (4) copy the player files ECPLAYER.DOC and
       ECQSTART.DOC to a directory for users to download.

    COPY THE PROGRAM FILES.  Create a directory on your hard disk to hold
       the program files (We recommend calling it \EC).  Copy the three
       program files (ECUTIL.EXE, ECGAME.EXE, and ECMAINT.EXE) into this
       directory.  Create a separate directory for the game files (call it
       \GAME01).  If you wish to run multiple player games simultaneously,
       create a separate directory for each game (\GAME01, \GAME02, etc.).





        ESTERIAN CONQUEST README FILE (Version 1.5)                    3

    DOOR-GAME BATCH FILE.  Create a door-game batch file that will run the
       ECGAME.EXE program.  Switch to the directory that stores the player
       game data files (\GAME01) before running ECGAME.  The command to run
       ECGAME must be include the path which contains the doorgame file.

       EXAMPLE OF DOOR BATCH COMMANDS:
       COMMAND:                 EXPLANATION:
       -------------------------------------------------------------------
       C:                       (switch to drive C:)
       CD\GAME01                (go to game directory \GAME01)
       C:\EC\ECGAME C:\DOOR     (from c:\ec, run ECGAME followed by
                                  directory \DOOR which contains the door
                                  file such as PCBOARD.SYS, DOOR.SYS, etc.)
       --------------------------------------------------------------------

    ADD THE MAINTENANCE PROGRAM TO YOUR BBS EVENT BATCH FILE.  Switch to
       the directory that stores the player game data files (\GAME01)
       before running ECMAINT.

       NOTE: Adding the ECMAINT program to the event batch file will start
       the game.  You should advertise the start of a game and wait several
       days to allow users to sign up for empires before adding this
       command to your event batch file.

       COMMANDS TO ADD TO THE BBS DAILY EVENT BATCH FILE:
       COMMAND:                 EXPLANATION:
       -------------------------------------------------------------------
       C:                       (switch to drive C:)
       CD\GAME01                (go to game directory \GAME01)
       C:\EC\ECMAINT /R         (from c:\ec, run ECMAINT and generate
                                   rankings file)
       COPY RANKINGS.TXT \BULLETINS
                                (copy the player rankings to your
                                   bulletins directory)
       --------------------------------------------------------------------


    PLAYER DOCUMENTATION FILES.  Make the player documentation files
       (ECPLAYER.DOC, ECQSTART.DOC) available to your users.  You may wish
       to compress these files with programs such as PKZIP.

       Esterian Conquest is now ready to be initialized.  Use the
       ECUTIL.EXE program to initialize a game (see the Sysop's Guide for
       information on running the ECUTIL program).













